      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six engine, delivering 333 hp through six individual throttle bodies and an 8,000 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec M-Variable limited-slip differential. The vehicle is mechanically robust; the dual-VANOS system has been serviced, and the rear subframe has undergone structural reinforcement\u2014a critical preventative measure for this chassis. The cooling system was recently overhauled with a new water pump and thermostat to ensure peak thermal management. Suspension geometry remains precise with refreshed trailing arm bushings. While the car shows honest wear consistent with a well-loved driver\u2019s car, it remains a structurally sound, high-performance machine optimized for linear power delivery and communicative steering feedback.",
